277
00:18:06,405 --> 00:18:09,645
This setup maps almost too cleanly.

278
00:18:10,035 --> 00:18:13,605
Each judge or each combination
of judges is an arm.

279
00:18:14,045 --> 00:18:19,085
When you route a task to an arm and
gets a verdict, you eventually learn

280
00:18:19,525 --> 00:18:20,875
whether that verdict was right.

281
00:18:20,965 --> 00:18:26,655
A human spot checks it, and downstream
test passes or fails, a customer

282
00:18:26,655 --> 00:18:34,025
escalated or doesn't So a better outcome
is a reward, and now you're in classic

283
00:18:34,025 --> 00:18:36,235
exploration/exploitation problem.

284
00:18:36,455 --> 00:18:40,495
Explore enough to learn which judge
is reliable for which kind of task.

285
00:18:41,205 --> 00:18:46,275
Then exploits that knowledge throughout
each task to the judge that has earned

286
00:18:46,275 --> 00:18:50,615
it And yeah, the tool I would reach
for is basically Thompson sampling.

287
00:18:51,005 --> 00:18:55,725
It dates to 1933 and has aged better
than almost anything in this field.

288
00:18:56,365 --> 00:19:00,625
The idea is to pick each arm in proportion
to its probability of being the best

289
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:02,555
one, given everything you've seen so far.

290
00:19:03,115 --> 00:19:07,325
And yeah, early on, when you know
little, it naturally explo-explores.

291
00:19:07,515 --> 00:19:10,285
It tries different judges
and watches the outcomes.

292
00:19:10,785 --> 00:19:15,095
As evidence accumulates, it naturally
concentrates on the judges that

293
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:17,095
keep being right for each task type.

294
00:19:17,935 --> 00:19:22,685
Agrawal and Goyal proved it achieves
logarithmic regret, as I remember,

295
00:19:23,095 --> 00:19:27,525
which in plain terms means the cost
of learning is small and bounded.

296
00:19:27,835 --> 00:19:31,545
You stop wasting calls on bad
judges quickly, yeah, not slowly.

297
00:19:32,205 --> 00:19:34,945
This isn't exotic.

298
00:19:35,175 --> 00:19:38,945
There is a solid body of recent work
using exactly this machinery for model

299
00:19:38,955 --> 00:19:44,475
routing, framing which model do I call as
a bandit balancing cost against accuracy.

300
00:19:44,475 --> 00:19:48,725
The same machinery transfers
directly to which judge do I call.

301
00:19:49,145 --> 00:19:54,765
And for this, an even more pointed
prece-precedent, a variant called

302
00:19:55,265 --> 00:19:59,565
QOC-aware Thompson sampling was built
specifically for runtime verification

303
00:19:59,935 --> 00:20:03,845
for the case where you don't merely
want the best arm on average, you

304
00:20:03,845 --> 00:20:07,725
want to guarantee a quality threshold
